"v.没收；充公 【英】 v. 没收，充公 (to seize private property for the public treasury) 【记】 con＋fisc(钱财)＋at e→钱财归大家→充公 【同】 同根词：fiscal(财政 的，国库的); confiscation(没收) 【例】 Confiscated property should be kept by the state for public use. v. 充公(由政府没收私人财产来作为公共财物) 【根】con共同, fisc财富－财富成为共同财产－充公 【参】fiscal(adj 财政的; 会计的); confiscation(n 没收; 充公) 【记】con + fisc 钱财→钱归大家一起→充公 【相关】fiscal 财政的 confiscate (v.)  1550s, originally, ""to appropriate for the treasury,"" from Latin confiscatus, past participle of confiscare, from com- ""together"" (see com-) + fiscus ""public treasury,"" literally ""money basket"" (see fiscal). Related: Confiscated; confiscating."
